>>HOFFMAN: Sure.

00:50:49.746 --> 00:50:50.814 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Go ahead,
whatever you have

00:50:50.814 --> 00:50:51.681 align:middle line:84%
to say on that before
I get to the last.

00:50:51.681 --> 00:50:52.749 align:middle line:90%
>>HOFFMAN: Sure.

00:50:52.749 --> 00:50:53.850 align:middle line:84%
The thing that people
need to understand

00:50:53.850 --> 00:50:56.853 align:middle line:84%
is that when you are
buying gold and silver,

00:50:56.853 --> 00:50:59.256 align:middle line:90%
you are saving your money.

00:50:59.256 --> 00:51:00.257 align:middle line:90%
You are not investing.

00:51:00.257 --> 00:51:01.892 align:middle line:84%
And the government
wants you to believe

00:51:01.892 --> 00:51:04.494 align:middle line:84%
that it's some speculative,
risky investment.

00:51:04.494 --> 00:51:05.962 align:middle line:84%
But in fact, it's
been the only way

00:51:05.962 --> 00:51:07.697 align:middle line:84%
to protect your
purchasing power.

00:51:07.697 --> 00:51:11.134 align:middle line:84%
Not just for thousands of years,
but for this past 10 or 15

00:51:11.134 --> 00:51:14.571 align:middle line:84%
years since the economy peaked
at the turn of the century.

00:51:14.571 --> 00:51:17.641 align:middle line:84%
It will be the only way you can
protect your financial assets

00:51:17.641 --> 00:51:20.811 align:middle line:84%
in the coming inflation as
it gets worse, no matter

00:51:20.811 --> 00:51:23.046 align:middle line:90%
what the propaganda tells you.

00:51:23.046 --> 00:51:27.317 align:middle line:84%
And I urge people to avoid
the paper PM investments,

00:51:27.317 --> 00:51:30.420 align:middle line:84%
Precious Metal investments,
and only own the real thing.

00:51:30.420 --> 00:51:31.788 align:middle line:84%
And to just give
me a call if you

00:51:31.788 --> 00:51:33.356 align:middle line:90%
have any questions about it.

00:51:33.356 --> 00:51:34.558 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:51:34.558 --> 00:51:36.026 align:middle line:84%
All right, now what about
the defense industry?

00:51:36.026 --> 00:51:38.428 align:middle line:84%
I mean, because that's
a huge part in the US.

00:51:38.428 --> 00:51:41.031 align:middle line:84%
Well, most industrialized
nations, that's

00:51:41.031 --> 00:51:42.499 align:middle line:90%
a big part of the budget.

00:51:42.499 --> 00:51:45.936 align:middle line:84%
What's going on with the
defense industry, and budgets

00:51:45.936 --> 00:51:46.903 align:middle line:90%
and spending?

00:51:46.903 --> 00:51:48.438 align:middle line:84%
How's that impacting
the big picture?

00:51:48.438 --> 00:51:50.173 align:middle line:84%
>>HOFFMAN: Look, it's
all about lobbying.

00:51:50.173 --> 00:51:52.109 align:middle line:90%
The big lobbies own the country.

00:51:52.109 --> 00:51:55.045 align:middle line:84%
The biggest lobby is the
health care industry.

00:51:55.045 --> 00:51:57.447 align:middle line:90%
And we got Obamacare.

00:51:57.447 --> 00:52:00.283 align:middle line:84%
The other big one
is the financials.

00:52:00.283 --> 00:52:02.752 align:middle line:84%
And the financials, basically,
have all the key posts

00:52:02.752 --> 00:52:04.087 align:middle line:90%
in government.

00:52:04.087 --> 00:52:06.823 align:middle line:84%
And then, of course, is the
military industrial complex,

00:52:06.823 --> 00:52:08.925 align:middle line:84%
which gets all
the wars it wants.

00:52:08.925 --> 00:52:13.029 align:middle line:84%
It has both parties asking
for increases in spending.

00:52:13.029 --> 00:52:14.164 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't believe it.

00:52:14.164 --> 00:52:15.966 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I understand the
Republicans have always

00:52:15.966 --> 00:52:17.200 align:middle line:90%
been into that.

00:52:17.200 --> 00:52:20.070 align:middle line:84%
But Obama coming out before
the sequester saying,

00:52:20.070 --> 00:52:23.874 align:middle line:84%
if we have the sequester, we
won't have military readiness.

00:52:23.874 --> 00:52:26.176 align:middle line:84%
And I'm going, we
already spend more

00:52:26.176 --> 00:52:28.945 align:middle line:84%
than the next 20
countries combined.

00:52:28.945 --> 00:52:32.849 align:middle line:84%
And we're talking about like 1%
or 2% cut in military spending.

00:52:32.849 --> 00:52:35.152 align:middle line:84%
And he, Obama,
the head Democrat,

00:52:35.152 --> 00:52:36.953 align:middle line:90%
is saying that we can't do that.

00:52:36.953 --> 00:52:42.092 align:middle line:84%
So they have a firm grip, these
military industrial companies,

00:52:42.092 --> 00:52:45.395 align:middle line:90%
on the purse strings.

00:52:45.395 --> 00:52:48.698 align:middle line:84%
And it's only a matter of
time per the quote you started

00:52:48.698 --> 00:52:50.467 align:middle line:90%
with before the next war begins.

00:52:50.467 --> 00:52:51.401 align:middle line:90%
Will it be in Syria?

00:52:51.401 --> 00:52:52.669 align:middle line:90%
Will it be in Iran?

00:52:52.669 --> 00:52:53.837 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, they have
to defend their existence.

00:52:53.837 --> 00:52:55.172 align:middle line:90%
>>HOFFMAN: Who knows?

00:52:55.172 --> 00:52:56.506 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You can't get a
budget if you don't have a war.

00:52:56.506 --> 00:52:58.842 align:middle line:84%
You have to keep picking wars
to justify your existence.

00:52:58.842 --> 00:53:02.345 align:middle line:84%
And as you say, for
those contractors.

00:53:02.345 --> 00:53:05.215 align:middle line:84%
>>HOFFMAN: I mean, Netanyahu,
he was quite for a while,

00:53:05.215 --> 00:53:07.918 align:middle line:84%
but it was because he was
running for re-election.

00:53:07.918 --> 00:53:11.721 align:middle line:84%
And now he's re-elected and
he's screaming louder than ever

00:53:11.721 --> 00:53:13.857 align:middle line:84%
at how not just we
need to stop Iran.

00:53:13.857 --> 00:53:16.693 align:middle line:84%
But we, the United States,
need to help him stop Iran.

00:53:16.693 --> 00:53:20.330 align:middle line:84%
So something unnerving is
going to happen over there,

00:53:20.330 --> 00:53:22.432 align:middle line:84%
particularly if oil
prices continue to climb.

00:53:22.432 --> 00:53:23.400 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:53:23.400 --> 00:53:24.868 align:middle line:84%
And people have been
having-- The eye

00:53:24.868 --> 00:53:26.770 align:middle line:84%
has been on that for
quite a long time.

00:53:26.770 --> 00:53:30.440 align:middle line:84%
And it is certainly becoming
more worrying by the minute.

00:53:30.440 --> 00:53:33.877 align:middle line:84%
Let me ask you about something
that you have on your site,

00:53:33.877 --> 00:53:36.446 align:middle line:84%
and I've seen a
bit of the trailer.

00:53:36.446 --> 00:53:38.114 align:middle line:90%
There's a movie coming out.

00:53:38.114 --> 00:53:40.116 align:middle line:90%
What is the name of that film?

00:53:40.116 --> 00:53:41.518 align:middle line:90%
We were talking off-camera.

00:53:41.518 --> 00:53:44.120 align:middle line:84%
You're going to try to sponsor
a showing of it here in Boulder.

00:53:44.120 --> 00:53:45.522 align:middle line:90%
But what is the nature of it?

00:53:45.522 --> 00:53:46.756 align:middle line:90%
Where is it going to appear?

00:53:46.756 --> 00:53:48.792 align:middle line:84%
And take a few minutes
to tell us about it.

00:53:48.792 --> 00:53:50.093 align:middle line:90%
>>HOFFMAN: Sure.

00:53:50.093 --> 00:53:53.496 align:middle line:84%
I mean, nothing appeals to
me more than youth asserting

00:53:53.496 --> 00:53:55.565 align:middle line:84%
themself of good
causes, especially

00:53:55.565 --> 00:53:59.636 align:middle line:84%
in this country today
where it's so misspent.

00:53:59.636 --> 00:54:02.672 align:middle line:84%
Partially because there's not a
lot of jobs out there, but also

00:54:02.672 --> 00:54:05.041 align:middle line:84%
because there's texting
and video games.

00:54:05.041 --> 00:54:08.178 align:middle line:84%
And I came across a group
of about three years ago

00:54:08.178 --> 00:54:11.548 align:middle line:84%
that decided-- I mean, the guy
who's running it is about 50,

00:54:11.548 --> 00:54:13.883 align:middle line:84%
but he has a whole team
of college-aged kids,

00:54:13.883 --> 00:54:15.752 align:middle line:90%
and 20s and 30-somethings.

00:54:15.752 --> 00:54:19.456 align:middle line:84%
And they've created this
full-length animated feature

00:54:19.456 --> 00:54:23.293 align:middle line:84%
called "Silver Circle," which
is kind of an action adventure

00:54:23.293 --> 00:54:27.197 align:middle line:84%
movie about rebels against the
Federal Reserve creating silver

00:54:27.197 --> 00:54:28.431 align:middle line:90%
to save the economies--

00:54:28.431 --> 00:54:29.299 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:54:29.299 --> 00:54:30.333 align:middle line:90%
I love it already.

00:54:30.333 --> 00:54:31.668 align:middle line:84%
>>HOFFMAN: --and get
sound money back.

00:54:31.668 --> 00:54:33.536 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, the trailer is on YouTube.

00:54:33.536 --> 00:54:35.705 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, it took them
three years and more

00:54:35.705 --> 00:54:37.941 align:middle line:84%
