some going into this kind
of micro-growing movement.

00:56:55.111 --> 00:56:57.080 align:middle line:84%
Agriculture is
becoming appealing

00:56:57.080 --> 00:57:00.016 align:middle line:90%
to some of the younger people.

00:57:00.016 --> 00:57:03.186 align:middle line:84%
I was wondering if
you had found any kind

00:57:03.186 --> 00:57:06.122 align:middle line:84%
of ingenious
breakthroughs among them

00:57:06.122 --> 00:57:08.191 align:middle line:84%
as a result of your
podcast and dealing

00:57:08.191 --> 00:57:12.061 align:middle line:84%
with them that are
inspirational for us?

00:57:12.061 --> 00:57:13.430 align:middle line:84%
>>HOFFMAN: Well,
I mean, it's not

00:57:13.430 --> 00:57:15.799 align:middle line:84%
like I'm following up
with them all the time.

00:57:15.799 --> 00:57:19.269 align:middle line:84%
They're slogging away
and I'm encouraged

00:57:19.269 --> 00:57:24.607 align:middle line:84%
by their optimism for
what they're doing.

00:57:24.607 --> 00:57:26.876 align:middle line:84%
But they're going to
have to dig-in hard

00:57:26.876 --> 00:57:29.446 align:middle line:84%
because it's not going
to be easy times.

00:57:29.446 --> 00:57:31.714 align:middle line:84%
Like I said, the
middle class has

00:57:31.714 --> 00:57:33.817 align:middle line:90%
been destroyed by inflation.

00:57:33.817 --> 00:57:36.486 align:middle line:84%
And it certainly is not going to
help the younger generation who

00:57:36.486 --> 00:57:38.121 align:middle line:90%
don't have much to start with.

00:57:38.121 --> 00:57:40.857 align:middle line:84%
But there are
opportunities out there.

00:57:40.857 --> 00:57:42.525 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I had to
remake myself twice.

00:57:42.525 --> 00:57:43.726 align:middle line:90%
I started out on Wall Street.

00:57:43.726 --> 00:57:45.094 align:middle line:90%
I went into mining.

00:57:45.094 --> 00:57:47.797 align:middle line:84%
All these businesses have been
hurt by government policies.

00:57:47.797 --> 00:57:48.965 align:middle line:90%
You can reinvent yourself.

00:57:48.965 --> 00:57:50.333 align:middle line:90%
There are good things.

00:57:50.333 --> 00:57:52.402 align:middle line:84%
There are things that are
expanding in the future.

00:57:52.402 --> 00:57:54.003 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And it seems to
me one of the things that's

00:57:54.003 --> 00:57:56.506 align:middle line:84%
coming up for them-- as you
say, a lot of them live at home.

00:57:56.506 --> 00:57:58.808 align:middle line:84%
And I see it as
another silver lining,

00:57:58.808 --> 00:58:01.811 align:middle line:84%
is the notion of
communal living again.

00:58:01.811 --> 00:58:03.813 align:middle line:84%
A lot of those kids
seem to be piling in.

00:58:03.813 --> 00:58:05.882 align:middle line:84%
I mean, we all did when we're
in our teens and early 20s.

00:58:05.882 --> 00:58:07.917 align:middle line:84%
But for longer periods of
time, even with children.

00:58:07.917 --> 00:58:08.718 align:middle line:84%
>>HOFFMAN: Well,
out of necessity.

00:58:08.718 --> 00:58:09.719 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Out of necessity.

00:58:09.719 --> 00:58:10.553 align:middle line:84%
>>HOFFMAN: Out of
necessity, people

00:58:10.553 --> 00:58:11.921 align:middle line:90%
will make the best of things.

00:58:11.921 --> 00:58:12.956 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So that means they
get to have company and someone

00:58:12.956 --> 00:58:14.023 align:middle line:90%
to dine with again.

00:58:14.023 --> 00:58:16.226 align:middle line:84%
I think that's a
delightful turn of events.

00:58:16.226 --> 00:58:17.794 align:middle line:84%
And Andy, I want to
thank you so much.

00:58:17.794 --> 00:58:19.729 align:middle line:90%
You're absolutely brilliant.

00:58:19.729 --> 00:58:22.832 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I learned so much in
